    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the overall body of evidence, including the Monte Carlo UQ analysis and five-point bench validation, provides sufficient confidence to support the regulatory submission. Although individual factor gaps were identified, the team judged that the aggregate evidence supports a Medium assurance level and an Accepted decision for the COU. Conservative safety factors applied to the hemolysis threshold are considered sufficient to compensate for remaining model uncertainty.",
